# Refactor Order Model (Table Splitting)

## Goal Description
To optimize the database schema and keep the [order](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/utils/database/crud_helpers.py#504-508) table lightweight (under 20 columns), we will split the potentially large [order](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/utils/database/crud_helpers.py#504-508) table into logical components: Core Order, Invoice, Check-in, and Audit Log. This improves performance and maintainability.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is a **BREAKING CHANGE** to the database schema.
> 1.  You must migrate existing data from the [order](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/utils/database/crud_helpers.py#504-508) table to the new tables (`order_invoice`, `order_check_in`) before dropping the old columns.
> 2.  The application logic in [order_service.py](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/services/order_service.py) and other services must be updated to read/write from the new tables.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Models

#### [MODIFY] [order.py](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/models/order.py)
- **Remove** fields related to:
    - Invoices: `invoice_number`, `invoice_status`, `invoice_issued_at`, `ecpay_...`
    - Check-in details: `frontend_check_in_at`, `backend_check_in_at`, etc. (Keep [check_in_status](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/models/order.py#204-212) if needed for quick filtering, or move entirely)
    - Audit/Cancellation: `edited_by`, `cancelled_by`, `refund_reason` etc.
- **Keep** only core fields (~15 columns):
    - [id](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/services/order_service.py#125-127), [order_number](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/models/order.py#102-122), `order_type`, `event_id`, `buyer_id`, `buyer_company_id`, `seller_company_id`
    - `total_amount`, `currency`
    - [payment_status](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/services/order_service.py#132-143), [status](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/services/order_service.py#144-155)
    - `created_at`, `updated_at`, `deleted_at`
- **Add** relationships to new models.

#### [NEW] [order_invoice.py](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/models/order_invoice.py)
- Model `OrderInvoice` containing:
    - Invoice details (`invoice_number`, `invoice_status`, etc.)
    - ECPay logs (`ecpay_request_log`, `ecpay_response_log`)
    - **New E-Invoice Fields**: `invoice_type`, `carrier_type`, `donation`, `customer_identifier`, etc.

#### [NEW] [order_check_in.py](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/models/order_check_in.py)
- Model `OrderCheckIn` containing:
    - `frontend_check_in_at`, `frontend_check_in_by...`
    - `backend_check_in_at`, `backend_check_in_by...`

#### [NEW] [order_log.py](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/models/order_log.py)
- Model `OrderLog` for auditing:
    - `operator_id` (User who performed action)
    - `action` (Enum: CREATE, EDIT, CANCEL, REFUND, CHECK_IN)
    - `old_status`, `new_status`
    - `reason` (e.g. cancellation reason)
    - `details` (JSON dump of changes)

